# Frontend environment variables.
#
# VITE_API_BASE is the base URL the frontend uses for all API calls.
# When unset, the frontend uses "/api" everywhere, which works for both:
#   - Local dev: the Vite dev server proxies /api -> http://localhost:5000
#   - Vercel prod: the serverless function in /api/index.js handles /api/*
# Set this only if you want a different backend URL (e.g. when the backend
# is hosted on a separate origin from the frontend).
#
# Examples:
#   VITE_API_BASE=/api
#   VITE_API_BASE=https://api.example.com/api
